[CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4sqXMwd.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/J7kJXEE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[OneDollaHolla]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Free Willy!!!!!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/tJfIBXr</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DYZVXeS.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/tJfIBXr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[notyourmuse]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>MrPuckett's new employee</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ox5QV1O</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cG0dxPB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I interviewed a new employee at work and I was excited to tell you all how he did</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3d9QT0Q.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The guy was pretty nervous in the interview, but he had perfect qualifications so I hired him on the spot. 

Let's see how he does in his first day</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xPGBw6e.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It quickly became apparent that he lied on his resume.

Typing 75 words per minute? No dude, all he could really do is just pound the keyboard and lick the desk</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ifpXUrh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He just blasted his music all day like he didn't care about any work getting done</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eJbznpl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Not only wasted his time, but he was a huge distraction for everyone else in the office</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SBCjs8l.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>HE EVEN FELL ASLEEP AT HIS DESK!

It's like some people don't know how to act at work it's crazy</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wTfXr5R.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>So he sat down with HR and had a long conversation about what it means to be a good worker

And I think it worked because...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MO64eyt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Then he was the happiest little employee we've ever had.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jy4DqL2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Next week it'll be 2 years since I adopted Puckett Jr from Nashville Humane</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RiirT1u.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Everything I did wrong with Mr Puckett the dog I've been able to do right with PJ

He's grown into the most incredible friend.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GX8qdpP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Not just the running - 2 marathons, 60 half marathons and over 2,000 miles in the last year

But every second he's doing exactly what I want him to do without me having to tell him.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hFENyeB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It's the first time I've ever raised a puppy

Every dog I've adopted had their own life before they met me, tendencies and behaviors that were shaped by their prior experiences</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ku73Kph.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>PJ is my mini-me - always on my hip and ready to cuddle for 8 hours or run for 20 miles at any given second

Nashville Humane not only rescued him, but they also posted him on Imgur and tagged me to say how much he looks like Mr Puckett. 

I went and adopted him without a thought the very next day, and it's one of the single greatest things I've ever done in life.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JpiGgy3.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I started fundraising for the Humane Association so they can continue rescuing animals like PJ and my hospice dog Nanna

I've never seen a shelter go to such extraordinary lengths to not only bring in animals from across the country, but also make sure they've got a loving home to spend their life in.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sR64zCI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>By @AmyRevives

While he may not be the best employee, he's grown into a very important part of my life and recovery. I can't thank Nashville Humane enough for making sure we both have the most incredible life ahead of us. 

I love you PJ, you're everything I could've asked for out of life and more. 

...

