(originally posted by @ThatOtherGirlYouKnow on 2021-04-30 07:24:15)</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Yx1041P</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThisTimeLastYear]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Stolen drones...heartbroken</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/V2NHxuO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SloxhCP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Our landlord showed the rental we are currently living in, we were both at work and it was fine, said he wanted to show the place to "SOME" perspective tenets. In the hour or so he was here, he let 14 or more people walk around inside our home completely unsupervised. The stupid Ipad was taken but more then that all of the highly customized drone equipment that we use on a daily basis for the most part was stolen. This stuff is hours, nights and weekends of work and focus...this is our outlet. My man loves FPVs and I support him whole heartedly. Its a controller, two sets of goggles, 14 or so batteries, all the tools and spare parts as well as a buletooth speaker and the RunCam. Oh, along with all the memory cards too. The community isn't very big for this stuff but it's been a huge relief and outlet for his mental health.
And someone just walked away with all of it, they couldn't possibly know what it means to us either. My man now feels like the winds have been taken from his sails, defeated really. Like this is years of work on these things. All of them were custom. I know in the grand scheme of things it's not much but the feeling of being violated is something. I don't even feel safe in this house now, we were supposed to be here till the 14th of May but we are not waiting now. 

And this guy, the landlord, is already a pain in the ass, turns stuff around on us. We got the cops involved, insurance and lawyers. I just needed to vent to the wonderful void that is this amazing community. You've all helped me so much over time. I'm hurt seeing my man, the love of my life, so defeated. I don't know what I can do to help him more either. 

Thanks for listening guys. I appreciate this space and all of you</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/V2NHxuO</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[707welshgirl101]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Président takes a Down sindrom girl to school</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/REB6R70</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5KJ1cZb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>. 
