https://secure.actblue.com/donate/demarcofordistrict1</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/xZeFMC3</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SoulonFire001001]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Tax the rich.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/aTlx7ZB</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UCye0bT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/aTlx7ZB</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lanhdanan]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I love all his movies.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/JtkWIUK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MD5KpGQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/JtkWIUK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DaShanghaiKid]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My Vi and Jinx cosplays?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/fYfVVsD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JX4oUP9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I know imgur totally hates selfies but I figure some arcane sisters are slightly worthy!! Instagram liked it so,,, here u go ! I posted wig tutorials for both of these since I’ve got a job with ardawigs now! ? @/nonbinate</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/fYfVVsD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mblackburncosplay]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Couple married onboard flight to Las Vegas when previous flight got cancelled</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/MyP2Ged</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ctVOj70.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Last Tuesday, Pam and Jeremy joked that they should hop on a plane to get married in Vegas. It wasn't long before both realized that the other wasn't actually kidding, so they booked a flight for Sunday on one of our competitors, with a Vegas wedding chapel appointment Sunday night.                                        Come Sunday, the couple arrived to DFW from OKC, just to learn their connection to LAS was canceled. But that’s when their bad luck ended.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HlXrmUw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Chris, another passenger traveling to LAS from DFW, overheard Pam and Jeremy discussing how they might still get to Vegas in time for their appointment. Chris also happened to be an ordained minister and offered to marry the couple himself! The three went online, snatched up the last three seats to Vegas on a Southwest flight, and hurried together across town to Dallas Love Field.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZLC8hXR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As they boarded the flight, their Pilot, Captain Gil, noticed Pam’s wedding dress and asked her about it (oh yeah, we forgot to mention: Pam and Jeremy were in full wedding attire, just for the fun of it!). Pam explained their story and joked with Captain Gil they should just get married on the flight. For the second time that week, Pam was surprised to hear the words, “Let’s do it!”</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nEpLLO5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Our Flight Crew sprung into action with toilet paper streamers and a snack mix sash for Chris. Julie, one of our Flight Attendants, stood in as Pam’s Maid of Honor. A professional photographer on the flight pulled out her camera for official wedding photos.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/usa7lO9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Another Passenger passed around an old notebook for the whole cabin to sign with well wishes and their seat numbers, which was given to the bride and groom as a makeshift guestbook.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/URe6CjO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Congrats to the newlyweds on a memorable inflight wedding neither our Employees nor Passengers are likely to forget! We can't wait to welcome you back onboard the love airline.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6KsUX8C.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Edit: providing source! Taken from Southwest Airline’s Facebook page.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/MyP2Ged</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Demmayyy]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Classic RATM</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/kfpUXJ2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/f4azrtt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MzT7d9N.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/kfpUXJ2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[YouWillAllReferToMeByTheNameBetty]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I take back everything I’ve thought about millennials</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/RYM1WTR</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eIVoHuB.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>At the bank with my son’s fiancé to help her get info on a mortgage. They told her she doesn’t have enough credit lines to qualify for a mortgage, despite them having a very solid debt to income and a hefty savings account built up. They want her to get a credit card and refinance her car (with them, of course) before they’ll consider lending  money on a house THAT IS LESS THAN THE RENT PAYMENT!!! I’m convinced they we’re leaving a worse works for our children and it drives me crazy.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/RYM1WTR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MuffinMuncher9999]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>